  "name": "detectable internal jugular vein",
  "description": "Visualization of the internal jugular vein on an imaging study, reflecting venous patency and normal anatomical course. Lack of visualization or incomplete visualization may indicate occlusion, compression, thrombosis, or technical factors limiting assessment.",
